COMPONENT NAME:IKM Netezza to File (EXTERNAL TABLE)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module. - Integrates data from a Netezza staging area to a file using external tables in truncate / insert (append) mode. - the BASE_TABLE option enables to specify the name of a table that will be used as a template for the external table.
Usages: - set "Staging Area Different From Target", and choose the logical schema of SOURCE model.
Restrictions: - When using this module with a journalized source table, data are automatically filtered to not include source deletions - The output file has to be accessible by Netezza server. - The CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE command only specifies the file format, which means all other options supported by this command are in default settings. The data file will be in the format specified by the default CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE options. For details about CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE options, please refer to Netezza Performance Server Database User's Guide.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Commit all data inserted in the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target file.

It this option is empty, the external table will be created with the structure of the interface target table. If a table name is specified, the structure of this table will be used to create the external table.

create external table ext_<%=odiRef.getTargetTable( "TABLE_NAME")%> <% if ("".equals(odiRef.getOption( "BASE_TABLE"))) { %> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "\t[COL_NAME]\t[SOURCE_CRE_DT] ", ",\n", "", "")%> ) <% } else { %> SAMEAS <%=odiRef.getOption("BASE_TABLE")%> <% } %> USING (DATAOBJECT('<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("WORK_SCHEMA")%>/<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("RES_NAME")%>') REMOTESOURCE 'JDBC')

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

insert into ext_<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "(INS and REW)")%> ) <%for (int i=0; i < odiRef.getDataSetCount(); i++){%> <%=odiRef.getDataSet(i, "Operator")%> select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "[EXPRESSION]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom(i)%> where <% if (odiRef.getDataSet(i, "HAS_JRN").equals("1")) { %> JRN_FLAG <> 'D' <%} else {%> (1=1) <% } %> <%=odiRef.getJoin(i)%> <%=odiRef.getFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy(i)%> <%=odiRef.getHaving(i)%> <%}%>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
